This is another way to edit the 'proportional' field in a PID loop. We're representing it here as a precentage so we're saying the value (output) is going from 0 to 100.
translation.variant: (change in input that results in P output of 0-100%)

translation.note: This indicates whether devices on other networks (i.e. BACnet, Modbus, N2, etc) are allowed write-access to the associated object. If this is not selected, the corresponding object is Read-Only.
This indicates a fixed 'CCN Force Level' used to relay a CCN write to devices on a CCN network. 'CCN Force Level' is a numerical priority that a write will be performed at.
This is the BACnet-exposed PID Microblock's name. PID stands for Proportional, Integral, and Derivative which is a well known control algorithm in HVAC and Process controls.
This is the minimum amount of time to allow the PID to go from 0-100%. This is used to prevent the PID output from changing faster than an actuator can move from 0 to 100%.
translation.variant: Min Ramp Time to transition between 0 and 100%

translation.note: This is the output update Interval of a PID Microblock.

This option instructs the PID to continually recalculate the Proportional Contribution of the PID MB, vs only recalculating it on the Loop refresh Interval when the Integral and Derivative are calculated.
This is the output value of the PID Microblock.
This is the output update Interval of a PID Microblock.
This is an optional input to the PID MB that is the Slew Rate control value.
This is the value to use when there are no schedules entered. (for all schedule microblocks)
